			"body": "<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: summarize by coderabbit.ai -->\n<!-- walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>📝 Walkthrough</summary>\n\n## Walkthrough\n\nThe command-sync flow now refreshes the search index after resources are downloaded by invoking `SearchEngine.instance().syncTables()` in both the CLI and doAction paths, with error handling that emits localised errors to standard error without interrupting the sync process.\n\n## Changes\n\n|Cohort / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**Search Index Refresh** <br> `packages/app-cli/app/command-sync.ts`|Added `SearchEngine` import and integrated search index synchronisation after resource downloads in ResourceFetcher flow, including try/catch error handling with localised error messaging to STDERR.|\n\n## Suggested labels\n\n`cli`, `search`, `bug`\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_override_start -->\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> ## Pre-merge checks failed\n> \n> Please resolve all errors before merging. Addressing warnings is optional.\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_override_end -->\n\n### ❌ Failed checks (1 error)\n\n|               Check name              | Status  | Explanation                                                                                                                                                                                 | Resolution                                                                                                                                                                          |\n| :-----------------------------------: | :------ | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------